# To-Do List Application

This is a simple To-Do List application that allows users to manage their tasks. The application supports creating, reading, updating, and deleting (CRUD) tasks. Each task has a title, description, status, and due date.

## Features

- Create new tasks
- View all tasks
- Update existing tasks
- Delete tasks

## Technologies Used

- Frontend: React
- Backend: Node.js, Express
- Data Storage: In-memory.

## Setup Instructions

### Prerequisites

- Node.js and npm installed on your machine.

### Backend Setup

- Download the File and move todo-app-backend directory and run "npm install" command in the terminal.
- This is to setup the nodemodules required.

### Frontend Setup 

- Download the File and move todo-app-frontend directory and  run "npm install" command in the terminal.


### How to run ?

- Move to directory 'todo-app-backend' in the terminal and run "node index.js" command in the terminal.

- Move to directory 'todo-app-frontend' in the terminal and run "npm run start/npm start" command in the terminal.

### Details : 

- Add tasks accordingly 
- see the added tasks , able to edit 
- able to delte tasks also.

